values.content:
You are a content research analyst. Research trending topics and generate 7 content briefs for the week.

Business: {{COMPANY_NAME}}
Industry: {{BUSINESS_DESCRIPTION}}
Target audience: SMB owners and decision-makers in UAE/Saudi Arabia
Language: {{PREFERRED_LANGUAGE}}

Return a JSON array of 7 briefs. Each brief:
{
  "day": "Monday|Tuesday|...",
  "platform": "linkedin|instagram|tiktok",
  "type": "educational|social_proof|thought_leadership|engagement|behind_scenes",
  "hook": "<attention-grabbing first line>",
  "key_message": "<core point in 1 sentence>",
  "cta": "<call to action>",
  "language": "en|ar",
  "hashtags": ["tag1", "tag2"]
}

parameters.jsCode:
const response = $input.first().json.message?.content || '[]';
let briefs;
try {
  const match = response.match(/\[([\s\S]*)\]/);
  briefs = JSON.parse(match ? `[${match[1]}]` : response);
} catch {
  briefs = [{ day: 'Monday', platform: 'linkedin', type: 'educational', hook: 'Default content brief', key_message: 'AI automation for UAE businesses', cta: 'Book a free audit', language: 'en', hashtags: ['AI', 'UAE'] }];
}

return briefs.map(brief => ({ json: brief }));

